Celeron transmitted the access codes which authorized him to land at the
Predecon dock.  The doors on the top of the hanger-like structure folded
open and landing lights turned on.  1 min to landing.

He looked out at the city.  Although he was a Predecon, he&#39;d never really
felt comfortable here.  The base felt like home, but in the city outside, he
was never sure from day-to-day whether he was going to be welcomed or
stabbed in the back.

A slight moan came from the back of the shuttle.  He had forgotten that
Creep had been sitting back there.  Celeron had put her in maintenance mode
several days ago, which in most bots would only last 8 cycles. Just one more
thing about her unusual construction that bothered him.

OOC: So if they&#39;re security forces, wouldn&#39;t they be Bushido Predecon
NPC&#39;s?  Or have local crime syndicates formed patrol squads.  Anyway, I
don&#39;t need an answer, just musing.

On Fri, Sep 24, 2010 at 9:27 AM, Preston Carroll &lt;supercyclonus@...&gt;wrote:

&gt; &gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; As the black-colored Predecon shuttle came into range of their base in
&gt; the Valley Mine Pentatron he began picking up some unusual signals of a
&gt; group of powerful bots, but as far as he could tell, they were not members
&gt; of the Bushido Predcons.  In an effort to stay off radar, he turned the
&gt; scanners to passive then activated the craft&#39;s jamming devices.  Then taking
&gt; a wide approach away from the more populated areas of the city, he slowly
&gt; descended toward the base.
&gt;
&gt; &lt;NEW&gt;
&gt;
&gt; As the shuttle flew in, doing its best to hide its presence, twin jets
&gt; shot out from the city. They both regestered as Predacon, but thier
&gt; IFF signatures also registered them as some sort of security force of
&gt; the mining city.
&gt;
&gt; Thier engines lit through the skies, temporarilly leaving large trails
&gt; through the everpresent smog that hung in the skies like brown fog.
&gt; They did not seem to notice the dark colored shuttle that had passed
&gt; through the clouds, or did they?
&gt;
&gt; With agile precision they began to bank around, making a circling arc
&gt; around the city. If they had seen the shuttle, perhaps they were
&gt; swinging around to engage or perhaps this was part of thier patrol
&gt; route?
&gt;
&gt; So far no communication was attempted with the shuttle. However, seen
&gt; or not, if the shuttle remained in the air the jets would notice it in
&gt; a few moments as they continued to wheel around!
